      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're on the right track! Vacuum leaks can indeed cause a lean condition code like P0171. To test for a vacuum leak, you can use a smoke machine or a smoke test kit. This involves introducing smoke into the vacuum system and observing where it leaks out. If you don't have a smoke machine, you can also perform a pressure test by using a vacuum pump to create a negative pressure in the system and listening for hissing sounds or using a smoke pencil to pinpoint the leak. Remember, the devil is in the details, and sometimes a small crack or loose connection can cause big problems. Good luck with your vacuum leak hunt!",
